title: $:/language/Help/inspect
description: Open an interactive REPL to inspect the TiddlyWiki variable space

Start a Node.js REPL (Read-Eval-Print Loop) with full access to the `$tw` variable space, allowing interactive exploration of the wiki store, tiddlers, modules, and internal APIs.

```
--inspect [<prompt>]
```

The optional `<prompt>` parameter sets a custom REPL prompt string.

The REPL provides:

* Tab-completion for `$tw` properties and methods, including function signatures
* Coloured output with smart inspection of objects and functions
* Persistent command history across sessions (saved to `~/.tiddlywiki_repl_history`)

!! Built-in REPL commands

```
  - .help            list all available commands
  - .depth <number>  set the object inspection depth (default: 1)
  - .history         show deduplicated command history
  - .history info    show the history file path
  - .exit            exit the REPL
```

!! Examples

Load a wiki and open the REPL:

```
tiddlywiki ./MyWiki --inspect
```

Load a wiki with a custom prompt:

```
tiddlywiki ./MyWiki --inspect "mywiki> "
```
